 <br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Strategy:<br>
I always bid 3. It does not really matter if I go first or not. This deck is designed to draw your 5 cards per turn (one with Gandalf at the beginning of turn, 4 during Fellowship). For this reason, I only include 1 copy of most weapons, and the mirror. All of my Companions have the Aragorn Signet, so Aragorn can heal 1 wound per turn on any of my companions. I play the 4 Elronds to get them as early as possible, the Celeborns are to heal Elrond to draw more cards, or the heal Galadriel if she has her mirror out. I only use one copy of the Release the angry flood as I can draw alot of cards, and Nazgul are not as popular in my area. I use the Secret Sentinels instead of Sleeps &#39;cause they can be used during Manuever, before most conditions can do any damage. I use no pump up cards, as my fellowship can handle pretty much everything that comes at them. I use Gwemegil to ditch extra cards from my hand to help in the drawing process. I use the armors to make Aragorn and Boromir effective against Uruk or the &#39;Rog.<br>
 <br>
My Shadow is based on trackers and exertions. The under the watchful eye adds an exertion every time you move, and they are cumulative. I then add the bowman who add an archery wound every turn, and they too are cumulative. Add in the Hates, and you have quite a killing machine going. I have the Tower Assassins in there to handle allies, and the one Memory of Many things is meta for my area, where allies are popular. Remember that with Arwen and gwemegil, I am able to ditch unused meta cards during battle. The Band of the Eye is there for a large minion when all they expect are the puny trackers. It is especially powerful when the opponent gives up a lot of twilight. The Enquea is there to shoot down large fellowships.<br>
 <br>
My site selection:<br>
Pony-To get Aragorn first turn<br>
Weather Hills-Adds 3 twilight<br>
Council Courtyard-this is where I try to play my companions<br>
Moria Lake-NOT UNDERGROUND!!! Also wounds Frodo or 2 others<br>
Bridge-Duh!!<br>
Galadriel&#39;s Glade-not much benefit to opponent<br>
Silverlode Banks-By now you should have hated thier ranger/you play 3 rangers<br>
Shores of Nen Hithoel-TWILIGHT and stops the double move<br>
Tol Brandir-Get at least 3 minions, Guaranteed!<br>
 <br>
I hope you enjoy the deck as much as I do!!<br>
